THE alleged killers of Zulu King Goodwill Zwelithini’s son Prince Lethukuthula Zulu appeared in the Randburg Magistrates Court facing charges of murder and theft. Tshegofatso Vivian Moremane (30), Margeret Koaile (42), Portia Mmola (28), Gontshe Tlholoe (30), and Dakalo Mbedzi (32) were found with suspected stolen items and they were seized from the accused’s homes. ALSO READ | PRINCE’S ALLEGED KILLED TO APPLY FOR BAIL!   ALSO READ | KILLER WOMEN STRIKE AGAIN! 